    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)
        System - Installation - EGR Cooler and Bracket - Exhaust Side
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>EGR Cooler and Bracket - Exhaust Side</title>
        <figure id="f145" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK17/K17022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Exhaust side EGR cooler and bracket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 30 stud bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust tube gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler clamp (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 70 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 nut (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0515" count="1">Loosely assemble the exhaust side EGR cooler, cooler bracket, and two new EGR
                cooler clamps.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new exhaust tube gasket on the exhaust side EGR cooler inlet flange studs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install exhaust side EGR cooler assembly on the exhaust manifold and install two M12 x 70
                bolts finger tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install M8 x 30 stud bolt and two M8 nuts and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the exhaust manifold was removed, torque exhaust manifold bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_153.xml" xrefid="s0608.1">special torque in proper sequence</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0608.1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two M12 x 70 bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_140.xml" xrefid="t335000502">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000502"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install all EGR system components before tightening the EGR cooler
                    clamps.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pre-tighten EGR cooler clamp nuts to 8 N&#183;m (71 lbf&#183;in).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen both EGR clamp nuts two turns (720 degrees).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten EGR cooler clamp nuts to a final torque of 7 N&#183;m (60 lbf&#183;in).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f144" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK17/K17021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rear heat shield, exhaust side EGR cooler</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Heat shield</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 20 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 nut (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position heat shield for installation and push down to fit in place.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install heat shield slots over exhaust manifold stud bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install M10 x 20 bolt and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two M8 heat shield nuts on exhaust manifold stud bolts and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_140.xml" xrefid="t335000502">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000502"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
